President Biden held a meeting with technology manufacturing leaders to discuss strengthening the domestic semiconductor industry and securing America's supply chain. He highlighted bipartisan support for the CHIPS for America program, which aims to counter China's aggressive plans to dominate the semiconductor supply chain. The President emphasized the need for the US to invest in areas like semiconductors and batteries to remain competitive. He also stressed the importance of investing in infrastructure for the 21st century, including water systems, high-speed rail, electric vehicle charging stations, and resilient grids. President Biden proposed the American Jobs Plan to revitalize American manufacturing, protect supply chains, and make America a leader in research and development once again. He acknowledged that the US has fallen behind in research, development, and manufacturing and called for bold investments to outpace global competitors. The President expressed his commitment to working with Congress and the technology industry to pass the American Jobs Plan and support American workers and communities.